blog.title: Poetically Confused
blog.description: An asexual nonbinary poet | They/Them Trying to figure out life

body:
@ all digital artists

I have a question that I hope to figure out, and perhaps you can lend me a hand!


Alrighty, for this question, here’s some background.

I have three screens: My laptop, my Huion KAMVAS tablet (which I draw on), and my IPhone.

My problem with said screens: They all show me different hues!

For instance, my laptop holds more of a colder hue (I think) than my KAMVAS, which has a warmer tint to it. It’s very confusing on what colors to choose, as the product of one screen looks very different from the other.

But that’s only two screens… Wait! There’s more!

When sending a finished, colored drawing to my IPod, the colors become even more wonky with over saturation and… I don’t even know what to name the hue issue, but it’s weird.

It’s given me quite a few puzzles which I’m hoping to find answers to:

Which screen (laptop or KAMVAS) is better to draw with?

Do others see my colored pictures the same odd way I see them on my IPhone?

Should I only post from my IPhone after altering pictures?

Can this issue be fixed? Lol

Anyway, I’d love to hear your input! I’m desperate, actually, hah, because I do love coloring, but this issue is very hindering! Any words of advice help!

Thank you!

— A fellow artist with issues
